    <item>
      <title>All Bushes Bloom</title>
      <author>goumaden</author>
      <link>https://gamebanana.com/mods/690762</link>
      <comments>https://gamebanana.com/mods/690762#PostsListModule</comments>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">5ad1abbdcff283808293ddd3033c755a89311b15</guid>
      <pubDate>Wed, 01 Jul 2026 19:49:10 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/6a456da805a79.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/6a456dd12b3e4.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/6a456de625a35.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/6a456e11303b9.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/6a456e2c5fc6a.jpg"/&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;h1&gt;&lt;b&gt;WHAT IT IS&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;This is a texture/model swap that causes all flowering bushes to bloom from &lt;b&gt;February 25th&lt;/b&gt; until &lt;b&gt;December 10th &lt;/b&gt;(AKA all seasons where there is not snow on the ground.)&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;I made this mod because I love playing god and destroying the natural order of things haha wheeeeeeeee&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;h1 class="SelectedElement"&gt;HOW IT WORKS (SIMPLE VERSION)&lt;/h1&gt;I made frankenstein bcres files where I took the "blooming" texture/model for every bush and squished them all together.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;This mod does not affect the timing of the in-game seasons. It does not affect any non-bush plants like trees or flowers.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;h1&gt;HOW IT WORKS (NASTY VERSION)&lt;/h1&gt;&#13;
&lt;details&gt;&#13;
        &lt;summary&gt;Click to expand&lt;/summary&gt;This&#13;
 mod specifically edits the .bcres files for season03 - season21, aka every season in the game that does not have snow on the ground/covering the bushes.&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;I've just merged the blooms onto the bushes, so you should still see the bushes slightly change how green they are to match the season like they do in the base game. (E.g., in fall they get a bit more yellow-tinged.)&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;The bloom models are a few bytes larger than the non-blooming bush models (due to having more polygons) so in order to keep the size of the bcres file functional with the game I deleted a few unused models that should never be used during these seasons (the partially grown snow-covered bushes.)&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;I doubt you will ever run into this in normal gameplay, but THEORETICALLY if you tried to place a partially-grown bush in your town and then used vapecord to set the season to 00/01/02/22 while in a season between 03-21 this might crash the game. But like. Why would you do that.&lt;/details&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;h1&gt;HOW TO INSTALL IT&lt;/h1&gt;Download the .zip file and check out the instructions in the beautiful README file I worked very hard on. :)&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;h1&gt;THINGS TO WATCH OUT FOR&lt;/h1&gt;This&#13;
 mod is mutually exclusive with any other mods that modify the same set &#13;
of objects. (Obviously, if you overwrite a modded file with a different &#13;
version of the same file you'll lose the original mod you installed.)&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;In non technical terms:&lt;/b&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;span class="RedColor"&gt;&lt;b&gt;Any&#13;
 mod you have that affects a natural outdoor object (e.g., tree, flower,&#13;
 bush, bamboo, rock, or stump) will be overwritten if you install this &#13;
mod, and vice-versa.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;In technical terms:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/b&gt;Any &#13;
other mod that changes any of the season03.bcres through season21.bcres files won't work with this one &#13;
unless you go through the texture changes by hand to manually combine &#13;
them and then recompile the .bcres. If you want to incorporate this mod &#13;
into another mod to make that happen I am cool with it and you have my &#13;
permission. :)</description>
      <media:content url="https://files.gamebanana.com/mods/acnl_all_bushes_bloom.zip" type="application/zip"/>
      <category>Flowers/Outside plants</category>
      <category>Skins</category>
    </item>
